                <article class="post-9079 page type-page status-publish hentry">

                    <section class="entry">
	                	<h1>Yasui</h1>
<h4>&ldquo;Do not pray for easy lives. Pray to be stronger men.&rdquo; <span style="color: #888888;">- John F. Kennedy</span></h4>
<p>Lucky for you, if you understood にくい, you&#8217;re going to understand やすい. It works exactly the same way, except the meaning is different (instead of meaning &#8220;difficult&#8221; or &#8220;hard&#8221; it means &#8220;easy&#8221;). Let&#8217;s take a look at the pattern, using our favorite verb たべます.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">v.stem + やすい + です</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">たべ　＋　やすい　＋　です</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">たべやすいです　＝　Easy to eat</p>
<p>That&#8217;s exactly like にくい.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">たべにくいです　＝　Difficult to eat</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">たべやすいです　＝　Easy to eat</p>
<p>At this point, there are two things you have to remember (for both にくい and やすい). Those two things are:</p>
<ol>
<li>The patterns (v.stem+nikui/yasui)</li>
<li>The grammar words themselves (にくい and やすい)</li>
</ol>
<p>Take notes and write these things down (or do whatever you need to do to remember them). These are the only two things you&#8217;ll have to memorize, and the only two things you didn&#8217;t know before starting this chapter.</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s practice a little bit before we get to the big practice &#8211; for now, all I want you to do is change verbs to v.stem+yasui form.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">ならいます　<a style="display:none;" id="ddetlink1330577866" href="javascript:expand(document.getElementById('ddet1330577866'))">Change To やすい →</a>
<div class="ddet_div" id="ddet1330577866"><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">expand(document.getElementById('ddet1330577866'));expand(document.getElementById('ddetlink1330577866'))</script></p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">ならいやすいです (easy to learn)</div></p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">みます　<a style="display:none;" id="ddetlink1419675100" href="javascript:expand(document.getElementById('ddet1419675100'))">Change To やすい →</a>
<div class="ddet_div" id="ddet1419675100"><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">expand(document.getElementById('ddet1419675100'));expand(document.getElementById('ddetlink1419675100'))</script></p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">みやすいです (easy to see)</div></p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">おくります　<a style="display:none;" id="ddetlink748828363" href="javascript:expand(document.getElementById('ddet748828363'))">Change To やすい →</a>
<div class="ddet_div" id="ddet748828363"><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">expand(document.getElementById('ddet748828363'));expand(document.getElementById('ddetlink748828363'))</script></p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">おくりやすいです (easy to send)</div></p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">かきます　<a style="display:none;" id="ddetlink1754156632" href="javascript:expand(document.getElementById('ddet1754156632'))">Change To やすい →</a>
<div class="ddet_div" id="ddet1754156632"><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">expand(document.getElementById('ddet1754156632'));expand(document.getElementById('ddetlink1754156632'))</script></p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">かきやすいです (easy to write)</div></p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">わすれます　<a style="display:none;" id="ddetlink833464619" href="javascript:expand(document.getElementById('ddet833464619'))">Change To やすい →</a>
<div class="ddet_div" id="ddet833464619"><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">expand(document.getElementById('ddet833464619'));expand(document.getElementById('ddetlink833464619'))</script></p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">わすれやすいです (easy to forget)</div></p>
<p>That shouldn&#8217;t be too hard on you, but if you need more practice, you can always look at your verb lists and chug through them. Next we&#8217;re going to look at やすい in actual sentences, like we did with にくい. After that, we&#8217;ll practice using both of them, and you&#8217;ll create your own sentences so you can actually use this stuff.</p>
<div class="woo-sc-box tick   ">By finishing this page, you&#8217;ve learned the grammar point やすい, which is the opposite of にくい. Now you know how to make verbs into &#8220;it&#8217;s hard/easy to do _____&#8221; phrases/sentences.</div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="../6-4/index.html#top" class="woo-sc-button  silver" ><span class="woo-">← 後</span></a> <a href="../6-6/index.html#top" class="woo-sc-button  silver" ><span class="woo-">前 →</span></a></p>
	               	</section><!-- /.entry -->

					
